  "response": "Recovering an IMEI after using \"fastboot erase all\" can be challenging, but here are some potential methods:\n\n1. Check Manufacturer Service Center\n- Contact your phone manufacturer's service center\n- They might be able to recover or regenerate the IMEI\n- Provide device serial number and proof of purchase\n\n2. Check Backup Options\n- If you previously backed up device data\n- Some backup tools might preserve IMEI information\n- Check previous device backups\n\n3. Original Packaging/Purchase Documents\n- IMEI might be printed on original box/invoice\n- Useful for reference or replacement\n\n4. Professional Recovery Services\n- Some specialized mobile repair shops offer IMEI restoration\n- May have advanced tools/methods\n\n5. Software Recovery Tools\n- Some third-party tools claim IMEI recovery\n- Example: IMEI Doctor, Dr.Fone\n- Caution: Verify tool's legitimacy\n\n6. Firmware Reinstallation\n- Flashing original firmware might restore IMEI\n- Use official stock ROM for your specific device model\n\n7. Contact Carrier\n- They might have IMEI records\n- Can help verify/potentially restore device information\n\nPreventive Measures:\n- Always backup device data\n- Avoid using \"fastboot erase all\" without understanding consequences\n- Create device backups before major modifications\n\nNote: Complete IMEI recovery isn't always guaranteed.",
